Source: edubuntu-meta
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Deepanshu Gajbhiye <gajbhiye.deepanshu@gmail.com>
Standards-Version: 4.1.4
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11), germinate (>= 1.18)

Package: debian-desktop
Architecture: amd64 armhf arm64 i386 powerpc ppc64el
Depends: ${germinate:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ${germinate:Recommends}
Description: educational desktop for Debian
 This package depends on the complete set of Ed-supported packages. It
 provides an educational desktop on top of Debian. It includes:
  * Edubuntu artwork and documentation
  * Preschool application bundle
  * Primary level application bundle
  * Secondary level application bundle
  * Tertiary level application bundle
  * Miscellaneous applications useful in educational settings
 .
 It is safe to remove this package if some of the desktop system packages are
 not desired.
 
Package: debian-fonts
Architecture: any
Depends: ${germinate:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ${germinate:Recommends}
Description: Additional fonts included on a default debian system
 This metapackage will install a selection of packages that contain
 fonts that may be useful for education or desktop publishing.
 
Package: debian-edu-preschool
Architecture: any
Depends: calibre, chemtool, fritzing, inkscape, kalzium, kmplot, ktouch, kturtle, lightspeed, marble, melting, pencil2d, rocs, step, yorick, ${germinate:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ${germinate:Recommends}
Description: Preschool Educational Application Bundle
 This package depends on all of the educational software for preschool aged 
 children that is fully supported by Canonical and the Edubuntu community.

